snippet.textDisplay:
Hey you guys! I have a recipe y'all might want to try. Just started watching you and Julien like a month ago and you guys inspired me and my husband to cook something different than usual. We are vegans by no means, however, we recently moved to Rwanda, Africa from the USA and have access to tons of fresh veggies.
What you need for Rwanda veggie soup:
1 can coconut milk
Water
3-4 cut up and skinned potatoes
3-4 carrots
1-2 onions
1/4 of a cabbage head
2 cups of peas
2 cups of green beans
4-5 cloves of garlic
1-2 green peppers
1 TBS of tumeric
Salt to taste
Immersion blender
Directions:
Cut up all vegetables into pot
Add coconut milk
Fill water until veggies are covered over by an inch or so
Add a healthy pinch of salt

snippet.textOriginal:
Hey you guys! I have a recipe y'all might want to try. Just started watching you and Julien like a month ago and you guys inspired me and my husband to cook something different than usual. We are vegans by no means, however, we recently moved to Rwanda, Africa from the USA and have access to tons of fresh veggies.
What you need for Rwanda veggie soup:
1 can coconut milk
Water
3-4 cut up and skinned potatoes
3-4 carrots
1-2 onions
1/4 of a cabbage head
2 cups of peas
2 cups of green beans
4-5 cloves of garlic
1-2 green peppers
1 TBS of tumeric
Salt to taste
Immersion blender
Directions:
Cut up all vegetables into pot
Add coconut milk
Fill water until veggies are covered over by an inch or so
Add a healthy pinch of salt
Cook until all veggies are soft
Add tumeric
Take soup off of fire and put on a hot pad on counter close to an outlet
Use immersion blender to make soup smooth
Add whatever you would like on the side.

(This soup freezes well to make a big batch and save some for a lazy day)

Love you guys and hope you can try it. ❤️
